                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>1. <hi rend="italic">Austro-Italian frontier</hi>.</p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer the question to the Deputies
                    who, after preliminary consideration, would hear the representatives of the
                    Italian and Austrian Governments.</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">Italian Colonies</hi>.</p>
                <p>Referred to the Deputies for consideration.</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">Italo-Yugoslav frontier</hi>.</p>
                <p>Referred to the Deputies for consideration.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">U.S. Delegation’s Proposal Concerning the
                        Further Work of the Council of Foreign Ministers and the Convening of the
                        Peace Conference</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The U.S. Delegation proposed: <list>
                        <label>1°)</label>
                        <item>that after considering German questions the present session should
                            recess until June 15th;</item>
                        <label>2°)</label>
                        <item>that the Council should now call a Peace Conference for 1st or 15th
                            July or, if this were not agreed, that it should be left to the next
                            session of the Council to decide on the date of the Peace
                            Conference;</item>
                        <pb facs="0415" n="393" xml:id="pg_393"/>
                        <label>3°)</label>
                        <item>that the revised Armistice terms with Italy should be signed
                            immediately;</item>
                        <label>4°)</label>
                        <item>that the question of drafting the treaty with Austria should be placed
                            on the agenda of the 15th June session, the Deputies to be instructed to
                            prepare in the meantime proposals for the consideration of the
                            Council.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to discuss the U.S. Delegation’s
                    proposal on the following day.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Ministers decided to meet at 11 a.m., 15th May informally, under the
                    chairmanship of Mr. Bevin and in his room, to discuss the German question and
                    decide an agenda for the other meetings of the day.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Revision of the Armistice Terms With
                        Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The U.S. Delegation circulated a redraft of the original U.S. proposal for an
                    agreement modifying the Italian Armistice regime (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 84<note n="44" xml:id="d134fn44">Not printed. The
                        proposed agreement on the revision of the Italian armistice terms, as
                        finally approved by the Council of Foreign Ministers on May 16, was
                        circulated as document <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 95, May
                        16, 1946, <ref target="#pg_436">p. 436</ref>. Differences between <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 84 and <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 95 are indicated in footnotes to the latter
                        document.</note>). Consideration of the U.S. Delegation’s proposal was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
